Package: CorNetto
Title: Knowledge-Guided Multi-Omic Correlation Network Analysis
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
        given = "Bradley",
        family = "Ward",
        role = c("aut", "cre"),
        email = "bradleyalexward@gmail.com"
    )
    )
Description: CorNetto provides a workflow for building knowledge-guided
    multi-omic correlation networks from normalized transcriptomic,
    proteomic, and metabolomic abundance data. The package supports
    group-specific correlation networks, prior-restricted sparse
    multi-omic correlations, differential correlation testing, rewiring
    scores, permutation validation, pathway-focused subnetworks, and
    graph export for downstream visualization. CorNetto is designed
    around Bioconductor data
    containers so that multi-omic assays and sample metadata can be
    managed consistently throughout the analysis workflow.
